metadata.comments: Grade 1-D:  straight-run fractions including kerosenes to intermediate distillates from mixed-base crudes;  used for mobile service such as trucks, railroads and submarines _x000D_Grade 2-D:  similar to Grade 1-D but with lower volatility., used for industrial and heavy mobile service. _x000D_Grade 4-D:  residual fuel oils blended with more viscous distillates, used for larger stationary installations. For additional fuel specifications refer to ASTM D975.
